A 9-year-old girl was reportedly shot when gunfire rang out at a mall northeast of Los Angeles on Tuesday night. The shooting occurred near a Barnes & Noble store at the Mall of Victor Valley in Victorville at about 6:30 p.m., according to KABC-TV. Shoppers and workers hunkered down in stores as the mall went into lockdown, the station said. The young victim was reportedly taken to a hospital in unknown condition. No other injuries were immediately reported. The suspect remained on the loose. The mall is about 80 miles outside of LA in San Bernardino County.